	"description": "Animations delight users. And you’d think, by the sheer volume of articles, that\nReact Hooks delight developers. But for me, fatigue was starting to creep into\nmy opinions on Hooks. \n\nBut serendipity saved me. I found an example that was a good match for React\nHooks, rather than just “the new way.” As you may have guessed by this article’s\ntitle, that example was an animation.\n\nI was working on a React application with cards in a grid. When an item was\nremoved, I wanted to animate its exit, like",
